  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Near infrared spectroscopy is a valuable tool to monitor cerebral oxygenation during
      intracranial interventions. However, it yields artificial results when the dye indocyanine
      green (ICG) is applied, which is routinely done for intraoperative angiography.

      The investigators examine, to what extent and which duration NIRS is disturbed following ICG
      application.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
